race.description: First National Real Estate Mixed Stakes
race.comment: RUPEE MC GRAW (4) had the drop on the lead early on but could only manage second, beaten 0.8 lengths (22.45) at this track in a Grade 3/4/5 over 395m. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Leading chance again. LENNY'S HONEY (2) missed the frame latest when sixth at this track (22.66) but scored four back at Murray Bridge Straight (16.52). Warrants plenty of respect. WILPENA (5) was a last start winner (16.83) at Murray Bridge Straight who is building a strong winning record. Has a good record here at this journey. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. LOCKABA ROCKET (1) generally performs well over this distance.
